    <thetext>(In reply to comment #1)
&gt; Good catch, if there is a patch by next week, I would be happy to review.
I have a patch, but it addresses only the case when the lhs is a name. It cannot handle any other case like super::new or this::new or foo()::new because none of them are recognized as constructor references. All we see is a reference expression of the form lhs::$missing$ in these cases.  Investigating how that can be fixed</thetext>
